    ScreenVeil utilizes the following core protocols to provide its utility:
  </p>
  <ul class="mt-6 space-y-4 list-none text-base">
    <li class="flex gap-4">
      <span class="text-blue-600 font-black">/</span>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-900">SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW:</strong> To render the screen filter overlay over other active applications.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="flex gap-4">
      <span class="text-blue-600 font-black">/</span>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-900">WAKE_LOCK:</strong> To maintain functionality during periods of display inactivity or dimmed states.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="flex gap-4">
      <span class="text-blue-600 font-black">/</span>
      <p><strong class="text-slate-900">FOREGROUND_SERVICE:</strong> To ensure reliable operation while the user interacts with other applications.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

